name: Edition #4 | Limited Box Set
description:
Welcome to the launch of Trunk Junk Edition Four, The Street Edition. Over our time of absence we took flight along side the wild imaginations of our favoured outdoor specialists, extracting and documenting inspiring and intriguing tales gathered from their individual lines of duty. This edition features the likes of Pose, Peachbeach, The Yok, Dabs & Myla, 123 Klan, Chris Garrison, Corbin Harris, Brett Chan, Charles Beckinsale, Jake Koia, Owen Wright, Dave Rastovich, Liam Gale and the Ponytails, Pirates Alive and many more Trunk Junk specials.

Limited Edition Box Sets include:
• Limited Edition Box
• Trunk Junk x Molotow D.I.Y Lighter Paint Kit
• 2 x Trunk Junk Stickers
• 3 x Alex Lehours Limited Edition Stickers
• Large Poster

name: Edition #3 | Limited Box Set
description:
Trunk Junk Quarterly Issue Three will be released 24 September, but is officially available for pre-Order. Please note that there's only 100 special packages available!

Issue Three hard pop top box package Includes: 120 pages of Trunk Junk, two large stickers, Art Park Journal #2, and a 'TJQ X Monaux' artist t-shirt!

Issue Three features, riders: Jimmy Roche, Tom Pelley, Ben Fawcett, Matt Gillings, Ben Currie, Mark Visser and more. Feature artists: Monaux, Matthew Skiff, and Soup Graphix Studios(Issue Three cover artists). Featured lens-sperts: Vaughen Brookfield, Brett Box and and film gurus Brain Farm Studios. Plus plenty more including our own Soul Sessions article, featuring surf imagery by the legendary Dick Hoole, as well as Trunk Junk Quarterly's first photography project "Bring Back Our Girls", and more!

name: Edition #2 | Limited Box Set
description: Trunk Junk Quarterly Issue Two packed a bang, with loads of interviews and articles on some of Australia's, as well as the globe's, biggest artists, riders and photographers. The special package comes in a Hard top box encasing 120 pages Trunk Junk, a hand numbered art print, a massively awesome poster by feature artist Iain MacArthur, and your very own 1/300 Limited Edition Trunk Junk Wayfarer-styled sunglasses.

name: Edition #2 | Magazine Only
description: Trunk Junk Quarterly Issue Two packed a bang, with loads of interviews and articles on some of Australia's, as well as the globe's, biggest artists, riders and photographers. Issue two featured: Asher Pacey, The Fine Line with imagery by the legendary Dick Hoole, Broken Fingaz, Amanda Mason, Eamo Donnelly, Riley Blakeway, Jack Mcoy, Cooper Chapman, Renton Miller, Iain McArthur, Thread Heads on the industry top clothes designers, Lotte Barnes, Jye Kearney, Time Slice Productions, Cloud Control and the Band of Frequencies.

name: Edition #1 | Magazine Only
description: Trunk Junk Quarterly Issue One was our 100pg debut on the market back on 1 October 2010. Issue one featured the likes of; Adam Haynes, Another Example, Ben Brown, Jack Douglas, James Jirat Patradoon, Michael Bukowski, Morning Breath, Pierre Lloga, Sirling Wraps, Stephen Bliss, Arron Petty, Dylan Pridaux, Isaac Buckley, Josh Hamilton, Julian Wilson, Matt De Nittis, Marc Triffit, Phil Bilingsby, Rober Macalister, and much much more!

name: TJQ X Monaux Tee
description: Trunk Junk Collaborated with local Brisbane artist Karl 'Monaux' Kwasny, and Coolangatta's PSI Screen Printing to bring you a 1/150 limited edition artist tee. The shirts are high quality and are a loose fit.
